description: • As a lead Intelligence Analyst at the National Air and Space Intelligence Center my duties were to provide direct threat intelligence information to operational US Air Force and US Navy flying units. • Responsible for several Central Command (CENTCOM) threat countries. Compiled and published detailed descriptions of foreign activities relating to future missile capabilities, threat country weapon system capabilities, tactics, training and employment scenarios. Reported findings are compiled in tailored Threat to Air Operations and Air Threat studies. • Briefed DoD leadership, Coalition Partners, aircrews and intelligence personnel on threat to air operations. • Supported worldwide JCS and national-level intelligence taskings. • I served as J2 Intelligence Analyst in Afghanistan Regional Security Command South, keeping key leaders abreast on tense enemy activity, necessary for critical combat missions. • Conducted Reconnaissance missions throughout my deployment, findings were integral to developing reconstruction projects in Kandahar, Afghanistan. • Fused graphic intelligence into daily Commander Intelligence Summaries. • Worked with DIA to produce portrayals of IED activity along frequented routes, to determine the threat to our operations. • Link or chart terrorists to terrorist organizations or events to determine activities and interrelationships. • Provide key leadership with the threat to Government of Afghanistan officials throughout southern Afghanistan.
